ll while familial ties that should have sustained them were broken at each turn. The book goes on to connect large-scale social policy decisions and their effects on family dynamics and demonstrates the limits of punitive justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCriminal justice, Administration of. 0aJuvenile delinquencyzPennsylvaniavCase studies. 0aJuvenile delinquencyzUnited StatesxPsychological aspects. 0aPoverty. 0aPsychic trauma in children. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066767740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520969087?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520969087423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520969087/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles